      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <div class="post-section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>The Google for Startups Africa Founders Fund provides equity-free cash awards to early-stage, Africa-based startups building with AI. The program is designed to help founders accelerate their product development and go-to-market strategy with both financial support and direct access to Google's technical resources.</p>
      <br/>
      <p>Awardees receive hands-on technical support from Google engineers, access to Google Cloud credits, and connections to Google's global network of investors, mentors, and startup communities. This is not a traditional accelerator — there is no equity exchange and no cohort requirement.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- REQUIREMENTS -->
    <div class="post-section">
      <h2>Eligibility Requirements</h2>
      <ul class="post-list">
        <li>Startup must be headquartered or primarily operating in Africa</li>
        <li>At the pre-seed or seed stage (pre-Series A)</li>
        <li>At least one founder must be an African national or permanent resident</li>
        <li>The core product must use AI or machine learning technology meaningfully</li>
        <li>Must be a registered legal entity (not just an idea)</li>
        <li>Cannot be currently enrolled in another Google for Startups program</li>
        <li>Founders must be able to attend a virtual pitch session</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- BENEFITS -->
    <div class="post-section">
      <h2>What You Get</h2>
      <ul class="post-list">
        <li>Equity-free cash award to support product and team growth</li>
        <li>Up to $200,000 in Google Cloud credits over 2 years</li>
        <li>Access to Google AI models, APIs, and developer tools</li>
        <li>1:1 mentorship from Google engineers and product managers</li>
        <li>Invitations to exclusive Google for Startups events globally</li>
        <li>Visibility opportunities across Google's media channels and blog</li>
        <li>Connection to a curated network of investors focused on African tech</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- APPLICATION PROCESS -->
    <div class="post-section">
      <h2>How to Apply</h2>
      <p>Applications are submitted through the Google for Startups portal. The process consists of three stages:</p>
      <br/>
      <ul class="post-list">
        <li><strong>Stage 1 – Online Application:</strong> Complete the application form with your team info, product details, and traction metrics.</li>
        <li><strong>Stage 2 – Video Pitch:</strong> Shortlisted founders record a 3-minute video pitch describing their product and vision.</li>
        <li><strong>Stage 3 – Virtual Interview:</strong> Final candidates are invited to a live Q&A session with the Google selection committee.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- APPLY CTA -->
    <div class="cta-box">
      <h3>Ready to Apply?</h3>
      <p>Applications are open until July 15, 2025. Don't miss this opportunity.</p>
      <a href="https://startup.google.com/programs/founders-fund/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary" style="display:inline-flex;margin:0 auto;">
        Apply on Google's Site →
      </a>
    </div>

